Quality evaluation factor: - Supply chain, Calculation algorithm: 30% for the "supply chain" factor as provided in Art. 8 of Law no. 315/2004 on regional development in Romania, as amended and supplemented, and it will be scored as follows: The supply chain is understood as the supply circuit involving a number of economic operators responsible for producing, manufacturing and commercialising the goods that are the subject of the product supply contract. The scoring will be assigned as follows:
a) for direct deliveries (from the original producer to the final consumer) the maximum score of 30 points is awarded; evidence is provided by any document confirming the right to produce and a declaration stating that the tendering economic operator is the producer of the offered product; if no document is presented, no points will be awarded.
b) for two economic operators (producer and intermediary) involved in the supply chain – 20 points are awarded;
c) for three economic operators (producer and two intermediaries) involved in the supply chain – 10 points are awarded;
d) Offers proposing more than three economic operators (producers and intermediaries) involved in the supply chain will receive a score of zero.
Note: to obtain the corresponding score, economic operators must submit within the offer documents confirming direct delivery from the original producer or the involvement of a single or two economic operators in the supply chain. If economic operators do not provide documents, no score will be awarded.

