Work guarantee period: The work guarantee period is expressed in calendar years and represents the extended guarantee for the works, i.e., the guarantee period granted to the executed works. Points for the extended work guarantee are awarded as follows:
- for a guarantee period of 6 years – 7.5 points;
- for a guarantee period of 7 years – 15 points;
Note 1: No points are awarded for a guarantee period of 5 years;
Note 2: For guarantee periods of works less than 5 years, the offer will be declared non‑conforming;
Note 3: The guarantee period is expressed in years. Fractions of a year are not scored;
In the technical proposal, the contracting authority’s form concerning the guarantee period of the executed works must be completed.
The offered guarantee period must be supported by specifying in the Technical Proposal the materials and technologies that the Bidder will use to ensure the quality of the work throughout the offered guarantee period. In the Technical Proposal, the Bidder shall describe how the Quality Plan will ensure the required level of quality of its results and work processes, by presenting the general approach and methodology for carrying out the contract activities (execution of works), including a detailed description of the work methods for the major components of the works and the materials to be used, so that the offering of an extended guarantee is not merely declarative to obtain a high score for this evaluation factor. Failure to present this information in the Technical Proposal will lead to the non‑allocation of the points related to the evaluation factor concerning the additionally offered work guarantee period.

Additional warranty granted to products: technical component, Calculation algorithm: The Contracting Authority awards points to offers that present a product warranty period longer than the minimum accepted warranty period of 24 months, as established in the tender documentation. The score for the evaluation factor "additional warranty granted to products" is awarded as follows:

a) for a warranty period less than 24 months – the offer will be considered non‑conforming because it does not meet the minimum 24‑month threshold required in the tender documents;

b) for an offered warranty period between 24 months and 48 months inclusive, the following formula applies: Offer score = [offered warranty period / 48] × 60;

The minimum warranty term is 24 months, in accordance with the requirements of the tender documentation.

Note: The offered warranty term will be the same for all products. Each bidder must submit a self‑declaration specifying the period of "additional warranty granted to products", signed, stamped and electronically signed by the legal representative, containing the warranty term expressed in months.

Note 1: Any warranty under 24 months will result in the technical proposal being deemed non‑conforming.

Note 2: No additional points will be awarded for warranties longer than 48 months.

Total score for the evaluated offer: P(T) = P(n) + Pt, where:
- P(T) = total score awarded to the evaluated offer;
- P(n) = score awarded for the "price of the offer" factor;
- Pt = score awarded for the evaluation factor "duration of the additional warranty period".

column3:
Factor de evaluare 3:
Demonstrarea unei metodologii corespunzătoare pentru obținerea asigurării că lucrările sunt realizate la parametrii calitativi solicitați (Planul de management al calității lucrărilor executate) (P3): Componenta tehnică - Punctajul tehnic al acestui factor de evaluare va fi obținut prin acordarea notei corespunzătoare calificativului obținut de oferta respectivă.
Punctajul maxim ce poate fi acordat pentru acest factor de evaluare este de 15 puncte., Algoritm de calcul: Satisfăcător - 5 puncte:
Planul de management al calității lucrărilor executate:
i. este prezentat la modul general și nu reflectă caracteristicile specifice ale Contractului de lucrări, nefiind în totalitate corelat cu metodologia de executare a lucrărilor și procedurile tehnice de execuție;
ii. este identificat nivelul de implicare al responsabililor din structura organizațională a Ofertantului cu controlul calității lucrărilor însă nu este detaliat;
iii. indică faptul că se realizează controlul calității la toate stadiile de punere în operă a documentației;
iv. există neconcordanțe minore între graficul general de realizare a investiției publice, activitățile/etapele realizate, responsabilitățile pentru execuția/gestionarea/controlul calității si resursele.
Bine /Adecvat - 10 puncte:
Dacă, în plus la calificativul Satisfăcător, Planul de management al calității lucrărilor executate:
i. este adaptat la caracteristicile specifice ale contractului de lucrări și corelat cu metodologia de executare a lucrărilor și procedurile tehnice de execuție;
ii. evidențiază adecvat nivelul de implicare al responsabililor din structura organizațională a Ofertantului și contribuția individuală pentru realizarea controlului calității;
iii. relația dintre graficul general de realizare a investiției publice/etapele realizate, responsabilitățile pentru execuția/gestionarea/controlul calității și resursele utilizate este realistă și în conformitate cu metodologia propusă;
iv. are un nivel de detaliere adecvat: facilitează înțelegerea propusă pentru managementul calității în contract la toate stadiile de punere în operă a documentației.
Foarte bine - 15 puncte:
Planul de management al calității lucrărilor executate:
i. În plus față de informațiile enumerate mai sus, în cadrul calificativului "Bine"/"adecvat", activitățile/etapele realizate, responsabilitățile pentru execuția/gestionarea/controlul calității și resursele utilizate sunt foarte bine definite, Ofertantul demonstrând optimizarea resurselor;
ii. nivelul și modalitatea de implicare a responsabililor în realizarea controlului calității sunt realiste și foarte clar definite.
Cerințele minime pentru acest factor de evaluare se regăsesc în Caietul de sarcini.
Oferta care nu indeplineste cerințele minime solicitate pentru acest factor de evaluare va fi considerată neconformă.
Oferta care indeplineste pentru acest factor de evaluare strict cerințele minime din Caietul de sarcini va fi considerată conformă dar nu va primi punctaj.

column4:
Evaluation factor 3:
Demonstration of an appropriate methodology to ensure that the works are carried out according to the required quality parameters (Quality Management Plan for the executed works) (P3): Technical component – the technical score for this evaluation factor will be obtained by awarding the grade corresponding to the qualification obtained by the respective offer.
The maximum score that can be awarded for this factor is 15 points. Scoring algorithm:
Satisfactory – 5 points:
Quality Management Plan for the executed works:
1. is presented in a general manner and does not reflect the specific characteristics of the Works Contract, not being fully aligned with the execution methodology and technical execution procedures;
2. identifies the level of involvement of the persons responsible within the bidder’s organisational structure for quality control of the works, but it is not detailed;
3. indicates that quality control is carried out at all stages of the documentation implementation;
4. shows minor inconsistencies between the overall schedule of the public investment, the activities/phases carried out, the responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and the resources.
Good / Adequate – 10 points:
In addition to the Satisfactory qualification, the Quality Management Plan for the executed works:
1. is adapted to the specific characteristics of the works contract and is correlated with the execution methodology and technical procedures;
2. adequately highlights the level of involvement of the responsible persons in the bidder’s organisational structure and their individual contribution to quality control;
3. the relationship between the overall schedule of the public investment/phases carried out, the responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and the resources used is realistic and in line with the proposed methodology;
4. provides an adequate level of detail that facilitates understanding of the proposed quality management throughout all stages of documentation implementation.
Very Good – 15 points:
Quality Management Plan for the executed works:
1. In addition to the information listed above (the "Good"/"Adequate" qualification), the activities/phases carried out, the responsibilities for execution/management/quality control and the resources used are very well defined, showing optimisation of resources by the bidder;
2. the level and manner of involvement of the responsible persons in quality control are realistic and very clearly defined.
The minimum requirements for this evaluation factor are found in the Terms of Reference.
An offer that does not meet the minimum required for this factor will be considered non‑conforming.
An offer that meets only the strict minimum requirements from the Terms of Reference will be considered conforming but will not receive any points.

