Duration of collection of cartridges and containers and registration in accordance with the WEEE Directive: The period during which the economic operator collects the consumables for recycling. The offered duration will start from the last delivery, i.e., from the date of signing the final receipt protocol with the note "accepted".

The activity must include the following stages:
- collection;
- handling;

The bidder must provide the contracting authority with suitable containers for the collection and recycling of the used consumables.
The containers will be supplied together with the first delivery of the consumables. Scoring for the evaluation factor "DURATION OF COLLECTION OF CARTRIDGES AND CONTAINERS AND REGISTRATION ACCORDING TO THE WEEE DIRECTIVE" (40 points out of a total of 100 points and a weight of 40% of the total award criteria) will be granted as follows:
a) For an admissible offer with a waste collection period between 6 months and 12 months inclusive – 10 points;
b) For an admissible offer with a waste collection period of more than 12 months up to 18 months inclusive – 20 points;
c) For an admissible offer with a waste collection period of more than 18 months up to 24 months inclusive – 30 points;
d) For an admissible offer with a waste collection period of more than 24 months – 40 points.

If the waste collection period is less than 6 months, the offer will be declared NON‑COMPLIANT.

METHOD OF PERFORMANCE:
Along with the Technical Proposal, the bidder must specify the collection duration of the offered product by presenting Annex 1 to the Specification Document – Quantitative and Value Aggregator, completed in column 8 – Duration of waste collection (expressed in months), accompanied by proof that the bidder is authorized to collect and treat WEEE, in accordance with Art. 34(1). All units or enterprises carrying out collection, sanitation, or waste treatment activities are required to obtain an integrated environmental permit issued by the competent environmental protection authorities (Emergency Ordinance No. 92 of 19 August 2021 on waste regime).
The supplier can fulfil these obligations himself if he is an authorized economic operator for WEEE collection/treatment, or through an authorized organization for WEEE collection‑treatment, in which case he must provide proof of the organization’s authorization and the service contract concluded between the bidding economic operator and the authorized organization.

The environmental permit must include the following waste codes:
08 03 18 – printer toner waste, other than those specified under 08 03 17.

Demonstration of an adequate methodology for contract implementation and adequate planning of resources and activities (MPR) – 15%: Technical component, the score (MPR = max. 15 points) is awarded as follows:

a) Lower rating “Acceptable/Satisfactory/Partially relevant” (5 points):
Within the proposed methodology for contract implementation:
1. Descriptions of the planning and execution methodology for the contract activities have been identified, but they are generic, lacking concrete information on the effective way of carrying out the activities, their logical sequence and any associated sub‑activities, in reference to the requirements of the specification and its annexes;
2. Personnel resources have been indicated in a general manner, without detailing their allocation to activities within the contract;
3. Technical resources have been indicated in a general manner, without detailing their allocation to activities within the contract.

b) Medium rating “Good/Adequate” (10 points):
Within the proposed methodology for contract implementation:
1. Descriptions of the planning and execution methodology for the contract activities have been identified; they contain information on the effective way of carrying out the activities but do not describe the logical sequence of them and the associated sub‑activities, in reference to the requirements of the specification and its annexes;
2. Personnel resources have been detailed by categories generated by activities, but the allocation to the operations set by the contracting authority has not been highlighted;
3. Technical resources have been detailed by categories generated by activities, but the allocation to the operations set by the contracting authority has not been highlighted.

c) Superior rating “Very good/Exceptional” (15 points):
Within the proposed methodology for contract implementation:
1. Descriptions of the planning and execution methodology for the contract activities have been identified; they contain information on the effective way of carrying out the activities in their logical sequence, with detailing of the associated sub‑activities, in reference to the requirements of the specification and its annexes;
2. Personnel resources have been detailed with their allocation to the operations set by the contracting authority;
3. Technical resources have been detailed with their allocation to the operations set by the contracting authority.

