Garantia suplimentara acordata produsului (fata de garantia minima de 24 luni solicitata prin Caietul de sarcini): Aplicarea factorului de evaluare se va realiza numai pentru ofertele care indeplinesc cerinta minima din Caietul de sarcini referitor la nivelul minim al perioadei de garantie pentru produs (minim 24 luni). 
Ofertele care vor prezenta valori sub cele minime solicitate prin caietul de sarcini vor fi respinse ca neconforme. 
Ofertele care vor prezenta valorile minime solicitate prin caietul de sarcini (24 luni), nu vor fi punctate, constituind conformitatea ofertei. 
Garantia maxim realista peste care oferta nu va fi punctata suplimentar este de 48 de luni. 
Garantia acordata produsului va fi exprimata exclusiv în luni intregi, a)   Pentru oferta admisibila cu cea mai mare perioada a garantiei suplimentare se acorda punctajul maxim alocat;
b)   Pentru celelalte perioade de garantii suplimentare ofertate punctajul se calculeaza proportional, astfel:
Ppuncte  (n): Pgarantie suplimentara produse(n) /  Pgarantie suplimentara produse  (max) X  20 , unde:
Ppuncte  (n): punctele obtinute de oferta admisibila evaluata pentru factorul de evaluare ,,Garantia suplimentara acordata produsului” (fata de garantia minima de 24 luni solicitata prin Caietul de sarcini);
Pgarantie suplimentara(n) : garantia suplimentara declarata si documentata in cadrul ofertei admisibile aflata in evaluare;
Pgarantie suplimentara (max) : cea mai mare perioada a garantiei suplimentare declarata si documentata in cadrul ofertelor admisibile;

column4:
Additional warranty granted to the product (compared to the minimum 24‑month warranty required by the specifications): The evaluation factor will be applied only to offers that meet the minimum requirement in the specifications regarding the minimum warranty period for the product (at least 24 months).
Offers presenting values below the minimum required by the specifications will be rejected as non‑conforming.
Offers presenting the minimum required values (24 months) will not receive points, as they merely demonstrate compliance.
The realistic maximum warranty beyond which the offer will not receive additional points is 48 months.
The warranty granted to the product must be expressed exclusively in whole months, a) For the admissible offer with the longest additional warranty period, the maximum allocated points are awarded;
b) For the other offered additional warranty periods, the points are calculated proportionally as follows:
P_points(n) = P_additional warranty product(n) / P_additional warranty product(max) × 20, where:
P_points(n): points obtained by the admissible offer evaluated for the evaluation factor “Additional warranty granted to the product” (relative to the minimum 24‑month warranty required by the specifications);
P_additional warranty(n): the additional warranty declared and documented in the admissible offer under evaluation;
P_additional warranty(max): the longest additional warranty period declared and documented among the admissible offers.

