Delivery term (P2): Technical component – the contracting authority awards points for offers that present a delivery term shorter than the maximum delivery term of 90 days. The delivery term must be presented obligatorily in number of days. The bidder must present a written declaration in which they assume the delivery term. Scoring is assigned as follows:
For this evaluation factor, score P2 will be awarded.
Delivery term score = (minimum delivery term * 20 / offered delivery term), where:
- the minimum delivery term is the lowest term among the offers considered admissible and it will receive the maximum points, i.e., 20 points;
- the offered delivery term is the delivery term of the evaluated offer;
- an offer that presents a delivery period longer than 90 days will be considered non‑compliant;
- bidders offering a delivery period of 90 days will receive 0 (zero) points;
- bidders offering a delivery period of less than 20 days will not receive additional points.
Note:
For delivery of products after the assumed term, a penalty clause of 10% of the value of undelivered products will be applied, to which the legal penal interest provided in art. 3 paragraph 21 of Government Ordinance no. 13/2011 regarding remunerative and penal legal interest for monetary obligations, as well as for the regulation of financial‑fiscal measures in the banking sector, with subsequent amendments and completions, is added. The interest is applied to the value of undelivered products for each day of delay, but not exceeding the value of the undelivered products.

