column4:
Extension of warranty period: The minimum duration of the performance guarantee is 3 years. For a guarantee period shorter than the minimum accepted duration of 3 years, the offer will be declared non‑conforming.
The extension of the warranty period is done by adding a full year (e.g., 3 years + 1 year = 4 years, 3 years + 2 years = 5 years). Points for the extended product warranty are awarded as follows:
0 (zero) points for the minimum 3‑year warranty;
10 (ten) points for extending the warranty from 3 years to 4 years, i.e., for one extra year of warranty;
20 (twenty) points for extending the warranty from 3 years to 5 years, i.e., for two extra years of warranty;
No intermediate points are awarded for intervals smaller than 12 months. For offers that allocate a product warranty beyond 5 years, the maximum allocated score of 20 points will be awarded.

