TECHNICAL COMPONENT
EMISSIONS STANDARD OF EQUIPMENT (NP)
Weight: 30%
Score: 30 points. The emissions standard refers to the standards established to limit polluting emissions of vehicles, especially cars. These standards are known as Euro standards. Scoring is allocated as follows:
For each vehicle equipment the following points are awarded:
  a) for NP – Euro 6, Hybrid, Electric – 30 pts;
  b) for NP – Euro 5 – 20 pts;
  c) for NP – Euro 4 – 15 pts;
  d) for NP – Euro 3 – 10 pts;
  e) for NP – Euro 2 and Euro 1 – 0 pts;
  f) for NP – non‑Euro – non‑conforming technical proposal; non‑Euro equipment is not accepted.
The score for the technical component is calculated using the following formula:
Pct = (N1+N2+N3+N4+N5+N6) / T

Where:
Pct = technical component score;
N1 = number of equipment with Euro 6, Hybrid, Electric emission standard × 30 pts;
N2 = number of equipment with Euro 5 × 20 pts;
N3 = number of equipment with Euro 4 × 15 pts;
N4 = number of equipment with Euro 3 × 10 pts;
N5 = number of equipment with Euro 2 × 0 pts;
N6 = number of equipment with Euro 1 × 0 pts;
T = total number of equipment used in waste collection and transport activities (e.g., 1 utility vehicle for waste transport, 1 shovel).
The score is calculated rounding to two decimal places.
NO INTERMEDIATE SCORES ARE AWARDED.

FULFILLMENT METHOD:
To award points, the bidder must, together with the technical proposal, submit supporting documents for each proposed equipment for the technical evaluation factor (identity cards, registration certificates, technical sheets or other documents indicating the emission standard).
If an offer includes more equipment than required by the contracting authority, scoring will consider only the equipment listed by the bidder in the Declaration regarding provision of vehicles, equipment and tools.

