Evaluation factor T2 – Total amount of reclaimed granular material reused in the asphalt mixture – Mrc: Mrc represents the total mass (in tonnes) of reclaimed granular material proposed by the bidders, calculated for the entire framework agreement, and is computed using the formula:
Mrc = X tonnes BA16 RAP × M BA16 RAP recipe + Y tonnes BAD22.4 RAP × M BAD22.4 RAP recipe
where:
M BAD22.4 RAP recipe – mass (in tonnes) of reclaimed granular material used to produce one tonne of BAD22.4 mixture, according to the BAD22.4 asphalt mix recipe with reclaimed material added;
M BA16 RAP recipe – mass (in tonnes) of reclaimed granular material used to produce one tonne of BA16 mixture, according to the BA16 asphalt mix recipe with reclaimed material added;
X tonnes BA16 RAP – calculated as: X (tonnes) = amount of BA16 RAP mix offered (in m²) × 7,200 tonnes / 75,000 m²;
Y tonnes BAD22.4 RAP – calculated as: Y (tonnes) = amount of BAD22.4 RAP mix offered (in m²) × 7,200 tonnes / 50,000 m².
Scoring algorithm:
- For Mrc ≥ 1,400 tonnes – 10 points are awarded;
- For Mrc between 1,000 – 1,399 tonnes – 7 points are awarded;
- For Mrc between 500 – 999 tonnes – 4 points are awarded;
- For Mrc > 0 but < 500 tonnes – 0 points are awarded and the offer is considered compliant.
Offers that do not consider the use of reclaimed granular material for the BA16 and BAD22.4 asphalt mixes (i.e., Mrc = 0) will be declared non‑compliant.

The bidder’s capacity to use asphalt mixes produced with a reclaimed granular material (RAP) addition, in accordance with the prescribed manufacturing recipes and technical specifications, is evaluated.
When preparing the technical and financial offer, the use of asphalt mixes with reclaimed granular material must not exceed a maximum of 50% of the total quantity of BA16 and BAD22.4 associated with the entire framework agreement – i.e., maximum 75,000 m² of BA16 RAP and maximum 50,000 m² of BAD22.4 RAP, which, at a reference density of 2.4 t/m³, corresponds to a maximum of 7,200 tonnes of BA16 RAP and 7,200 tonnes of BAD22.4 RAP.
- "Granular material" means natural/crushed sand, graded aggregate fractions;
- According to the specifications, chapter 2.20, bidders must submit the standard recipes for the asphalt mixes used, certified by an authorized laboratory.
Thus, bidders shall submit, for each mix type BAD22.4 and BA16:
- a standard recipe – for 1 tonne of asphalt mix without reclaimed granular material;
- a framework recipe (RAP recipe) – for 1 tonne of asphalt mix with reclaimed granular material.
Bidders shall indicate, in the technical offer, the quantities of reclaimed mix offered for BA16 RAP and BAD22.4 RAP, corresponding to the maximum quantities in the framework agreement – expressed both in m² and in tonnes (using the X and Y formulas above).
To convert the offered reclaimed‑mix quantities from m² to tonnes, the following formulas are used:
X tonnes BA16 RAP – total amount of BA16 RAP mix offered, in tonnes, calculated from the offered area (m²) entered by the bidder on line 7 of Form 8 – Offer, Annex 2 – and computed as:
X (tonnes) = BA16 RAP mix offered (m²) × 7,200 tonnes / 75,000 m².
Y tonnes BAD22.4 RAP – total amount of BAD22.4 RAP mix offered, in tonnes, calculated from the offered area (m²) entered by the bidder on line 10 of Form 8 – Offer, Annex 2 – and computed as:
Y (tonnes) = BAD22.4 RAP mix offered (m²) × 7,200 tonnes / 50,000 m².
Reused materials may be included in the BAD22.4 and BA16 mix recipes in the following proportions:
- up to 20% in BAD22.4 layers;
- up to 10% in the BA16 wearing layer.
The use of reclaimed asphalt mixes is not accepted for the production of MASF16.

