Supply chain: Technical component, a) The highest score is awarded to direct deliveries (the bidder is the manufacturer) — 60 points; 
b) For deliveries with a single economic operator involved in the supply chain between the producer and the final consumer (one intermediary) — 30 points; 
c) For deliveries with two or more economic operators involved in the supply chain between the producer and the final consumer (two or more intermediaries) — 0 points;
The score is calculated individually for each product, and the total score (Pf) is calculated using the following formula:
Pf = (score product 1 + score product 2 + … + score product n‑1 + score product n) / n, where n is the number of products.

Method of fulfilment:

To demonstrate the evaluation factor "Supply chain", bidders shall clearly indicate (by completing the Technical Proposal Form) for each product the name of the manufacturer.

To demonstrate the number of intermediaries in the supply chain and product delivery, bidders are required to submit at the technical proposal level: a) Manufacturer certificate / manufacturing licence / manufacturing authorisation and/or other supporting documents for the product(s) that are the object of the purchase, if the manufacturer participates in the procedure (the bidder is the manufacturer) and/or b) Contract concluded between the bidder and the manufacturer showing that the products object of the purchase are covered, accompanied by the manufacturer certificate / manufacturing licence / authorisation and/or other supporting documents from the manufacturer for the respective products, bearing the note "Conforms to the original", if the bidder is the first intermediary in the supply chain. Calculation algorithm: Points are awarded for each product individually as follows: a) No intermediary in the supply chain (i.e., direct offer from the manufacturer): 60 points; b) One intermediary in the supply chain (i.e., the bidder purchases directly from the manufacturer): 30 points; c) Two or more intermediaries in the supply chain (i.e., the bidder purchases from distributors or other suppliers): 0 points.

If economic operators do not submit the required documents, no points will be awarded.
THE SUPPORTING DOCUMENTS TO DEMONSTRATE THE NUMBER OF INTERMEDIARIES IN THE SUPPLY CHAIN MUST BE SUBMITTED WITH THE TECHNICAL OFFER.

